cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.RO

This paper is about scene modeling using a hybrid Boltzmann Machine, which is a popular technique in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves integrating relations between objects, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. The use of Boltzmann Machines also suggests that the paper could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the evaluation of the method on a scene classification dataset could make it relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, since the paper is about scene modeling for robots, it could also be relevant to cs.RO (Robotics).
